and the Ebon Storm.  And, although the first assault<br>
was turned back, two later assaults had succeeded.<br>
<br>
The Clockwork King was soon rebuilt, but the ashes of <br>
Tinker's Pride had been permanently scattered to the winds,<br>
its members slowly finding new homes and friendships.<br>
<br>
Gneen sat in a friendly Tavern and wondered what had <br>
happened to Charizma, for apparently Apep's rage had<br>
been soothed somehow and the remaining cities were<br>
safe until the next tantrum arose.<br>
<br>
&quot;I guess it is not for me to know.&quot; he though.  He put aside<br>
his journal for the moment - always ready to add another<br>
chapter should information somehow come his way.<br>
